Bharat Petroleum Corp. (BPCL) ,  India â€™s
second-largest state refiner, bought 2 million barrels of
Angolan Nemba crude via a tender from Vitol Group for loading in
January, said two traders with knowledge of the matter.  The company also purchased 1 million barrels of Libyan
Mellitah blend from Total SA, the people said, asking not to be
identified because the information is confidential.  Bharat Petroleum had bought 1 million barrels each of
Nemba, Mellitah and Nigerian Akpo grades for loading in
December, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporters on this story:
